WEBVTT

00:08.367 --> 00:09.435
Dang.

00:09.468 --> 00:12.571
What in Grod's name
am I looking at?

00:14.173 --> 00:15.541
Fire,

00:15.574 --> 00:17.142
ice,

00:17.176 --> 00:18.477
candy,

00:18.511 --> 00:19.912
and slime.

00:21.247 --> 00:22.281
Weird.

00:22.315 --> 00:24.217
How did this happen, Ice King?

00:24.250 --> 00:26.619
Look, I know it's a lot
to take in.

00:26.652 --> 00:28.354
Let's go to the living room.

00:32.725 --> 00:34.026
[ Whoosh ]

00:34.059 --> 00:36.295
Now settle in,
get comfortable,

00:36.329 --> 00:40.499
'cause I am gonna tell you
everything.

00:40.533 --> 00:44.169
And it is going to
blow your -- Oop!

00:44.203 --> 00:48.207
I gotta kiss my skyhooks
good night.

00:48.241 --> 00:50.243
Good night, my skookie-wooks.

00:50.276 --> 00:52.177
[ Kisses ]

00:52.211 --> 00:54.179
Okay.

00:54.213 --> 00:55.314
Dude...

00:55.348 --> 00:58.083
Why does it look like
a four-way pizza?!

00:58.116 --> 00:59.985
Is everyone in Ooo
like a zombie?

01:00.018 --> 01:01.420
Is everyone basically dead?

01:01.454 --> 01:05.558
Everyone is not dead.
It's much worse.

01:06.759 --> 01:10.429
Let me
start at the beginning.

01:10.463 --> 01:13.198
No.

01:13.232 --> 01:16.269
What am I gonna do without
my besties around?

01:20.306 --> 01:22.408
Mm.

01:22.441 --> 01:25.478
♪♪

01:30.148 --> 01:33.619
Mm, okay.
Bird watching sounds cool.

01:33.652 --> 01:37.290
Hey, roomie! I'm going out to
pick up some magic ingredients.

01:37.323 --> 01:40.092
Ooh! Are you making
somethin' delicious?

01:40.125 --> 01:41.627
Oh, I'm building
a magic battery to power

01:41.660 --> 01:43.796
my elemental purification spell.

01:43.829 --> 01:45.898
Cool. Bring me a snackie.

01:45.931 --> 01:47.966
Like...a doughnut?

01:48.000 --> 01:49.535
Surprise me.

01:49.568 --> 01:51.069
Oh, I'll surprise you.

01:51.103 --> 01:54.573
[ Under breath ]
I'll surprise everyone.

01:54.607 --> 01:56.609
Wait. What was Patience
talking about?

01:56.642 --> 01:59.878
Oh, it's not important.
Something ominous.

01:59.912 --> 02:04.483
Anyways, it was then that
I really got into bird watching.

02:08.921 --> 02:12.825
♪♪

02:12.858 --> 02:15.561
What else we got here?

02:15.594 --> 02:16.795
A penguin.

02:16.829 --> 02:19.632
Oh. Right.

02:19.665 --> 02:21.434
[ Gasps ] Something!

02:23.469 --> 02:25.604
Is that...

02:25.638 --> 02:29.375
Oh...my...glaah!

02:31.009 --> 02:32.611
[ Gasps ]

02:32.645 --> 02:34.146
You a toucan?

02:34.179 --> 02:37.082
Simon, I've been trying so hard
to help you.

02:37.115 --> 02:39.685
I've tried reprogramming--nnn
your -- your crown,

02:39.718 --> 02:42.020
Code-mapping, penguin-napping,
co-mingling with magic,

02:42.054 --> 02:43.255
and grasping and grappling,

02:43.288 --> 02:44.857
but it just hasn't
been happening.

02:44.890 --> 02:47.526
It's saddening, it's maddening,
and I'm rapping and -- and...

02:47.560 --> 02:50.463
[ Inhales deeply ]

02:50.496 --> 02:51.964
[ Inhales ]

02:51.997 --> 02:53.699
So I'm trying
the direct approach.

02:53.732 --> 02:55.501
Ugh.
Wenk!

02:55.534 --> 03:00.005
No, I don't remember who she is,
but I know how to find out.

03:00.038 --> 03:01.840
Hey!

03:01.874 --> 03:04.510
So good to see you!

03:04.543 --> 03:07.780
You still working
at that same place?

03:07.813 --> 03:10.148
Mm, my work takes me all over.

03:10.182 --> 03:13.218
I meant all over the place.

03:13.251 --> 03:16.655
Oh! Before I forget,
I just got a new phone.

03:16.689 --> 03:20.726
Would you mind reentering
your info for me?

03:20.759 --> 03:23.396
It's okay.
I know you don't remember me.

03:23.429 --> 03:25.330
No, no, no. I can get this.

03:25.364 --> 03:28.834
[ Inhales slowly, pfft! ]

03:28.867 --> 03:30.403
I lost it.

03:30.436 --> 03:34.239
A long time ago,
you and I were...colleagues.

03:34.272 --> 03:36.375
My name is Betty Grof, and --

03:36.409 --> 03:39.912
That's what I was gonna say!
Betty!

03:39.945 --> 03:41.580
[ Inhales ]

03:41.614 --> 03:43.549
Hey, do you wanna go
on a date with me tonight?

03:43.582 --> 03:47.420
[ Babbles ]
Uh, buh, buh, buh. Yes.

03:47.453 --> 03:51.356
Meet me at 8:00
at my Magic Man House.

03:57.696 --> 04:00.433
[ Laughing ]

04:00.466 --> 04:02.435
♪♪

04:02.468 --> 04:05.037
[ Ring ]

04:05.070 --> 04:06.539
Hello?

04:06.572 --> 04:08.907
You are not gonna believe
what just happened.

04:08.941 --> 04:10.175
What?

04:10.208 --> 04:11.844
A lady touched me!

04:11.877 --> 04:13.278
That's cool. Who is she?

04:13.311 --> 04:15.714
I think she might be
an exotic bird.

04:15.748 --> 04:19.117
But guess who's going
on a date tonight!

04:19.151 --> 04:21.620
Wow. So what are you
gonna wear?

04:21.654 --> 04:24.557
Oh, probably my go-to --
blue muumuu.

04:24.590 --> 04:26.058
Ugh!

04:26.091 --> 04:28.961
No! You need to get
a nice bespoked suit.

04:28.994 --> 04:31.464
A be-wudda-wa?

04:31.497 --> 04:35.300
"Bespoke" means it's custom-made
to fit your specific dimensions

04:35.333 --> 04:38.571
and emphasize what's flattering
about your shape.

04:38.604 --> 04:39.772
Like my abs.

04:39.805 --> 04:42.140
No, I'd say you're kinda
bottom-heavy.

04:42.174 --> 04:44.276
No, that's just the muumuu,
dawg.

04:44.309 --> 04:45.711
I'm jacked.

04:45.744 --> 04:49.147
Hmm.

04:49.181 --> 04:51.049
Oh, yeah.

04:51.083 --> 04:53.285
What the heck d--
Shh!

04:53.318 --> 04:56.755
'Kay, so then we went
suit shopping.

04:56.789 --> 05:00.993
It's very important to pick
a good, natural fabric.

05:01.026 --> 05:02.661
As for color, for a first suit,

05:02.695 --> 05:05.464
you should choose between black,
navy, or charcoal grey.

05:05.498 --> 05:06.765
Why?

05:06.799 --> 05:08.601
It's a wizard fashion rule.

05:08.634 --> 05:10.503
If you stray, you'll look
like a fool.

05:10.536 --> 05:13.071
How's about if I make my suit
a onesie?

05:13.105 --> 05:14.707
[ Smack ]
Ow!

05:17.843 --> 05:20.979
Whoa.

05:21.013 --> 05:24.082
Let's get to work!

05:24.116 --> 05:28.854
♪♪

05:28.887 --> 05:31.857
And then Life-Giving Magus
checked an even darker...

05:31.890 --> 05:34.292
[ Whispers ] What is going on?
...shade of gray against
my face.

05:34.326 --> 05:36.929
Until finally...

05:36.962 --> 05:38.463
Life-Giving Magus: Yep!

05:41.534 --> 05:44.202
Pretty fly for an ice guy.

05:44.236 --> 05:47.472
♪♪

05:52.010 --> 05:55.213
Male voice: [ Singsongy ]
Ding dong! Someone's here!

05:55.247 --> 05:57.883
That's clever.

05:57.916 --> 05:59.618
Hello, Simon.

05:59.652 --> 06:01.286
Uh, flowers.

06:01.319 --> 06:02.621
Come in. Come in.

06:02.655 --> 06:04.957
I really like how
you decorated the place.

06:04.990 --> 06:08.293
I'm really into skulls
and old teeth in jars, too.

06:08.326 --> 06:10.462
Ready for our date?

06:10.495 --> 06:12.731
You bet.

06:12.765 --> 06:14.066
Bah-bam!

06:14.099 --> 06:17.169
Aaaaah!

06:17.202 --> 06:20.305
[ Pants ] This a-way.

06:20.338 --> 06:22.641
What is this place?

06:22.675 --> 06:24.677
In the old days,
we would meet here,

06:24.710 --> 06:27.312
and you would give me books
because you had a subscription

06:27.345 --> 06:28.881
to the Book a Day Club.

06:28.914 --> 06:30.415
Book a Day?

06:30.448 --> 06:32.084
You gave me the excess books
because I was associated

06:32.117 --> 06:33.886
with Books for the Bookless.

06:33.919 --> 06:36.722
[ Laughs ] Simon!
You want your usual booth?

06:36.755 --> 06:41.193
Bogo! You remember him?
Lead the way, Bogo!

06:43.896 --> 06:45.497
So...

06:45.530 --> 06:47.332
Yes?

06:47.365 --> 06:49.101
Are we going splitsies?

06:49.134 --> 06:50.603
[ Sighs ]

06:50.636 --> 06:52.905
Okay, I'll pay for half
your entrée.

06:52.938 --> 06:56.208
But if you get an appy
or a dessert, it's on you.

06:57.643 --> 06:58.844
Mmm, mmm, mmm!

06:58.877 --> 07:00.278
[ Smacks lips ]

07:00.312 --> 07:02.615
[ Inhaling deeply ] Aah!

07:02.648 --> 07:04.717
What? There something
in my beard?

07:04.750 --> 07:07.452
You don't remember any of this?

07:07.485 --> 07:09.755
[ Thinking ] She's starting
to freak me out.

07:09.788 --> 07:11.523
Ring, ring!

07:11.556 --> 07:13.425
Sorry. I should take this.

07:13.458 --> 07:17.095
Oh, hi, Gunter.
No. I'm on my date.

07:17.129 --> 07:19.297
[ Inhaling deeply ]

07:19.331 --> 07:20.766
Gunter, I have to go.

07:20.799 --> 07:22.567
[ Chomping ]

07:22.601 --> 07:24.202
Technology, right? [ Chuckles ]

07:24.236 --> 07:27.072
Aah! No!

07:27.105 --> 07:28.440
[ Zapping ]
It's all wrong!

07:28.473 --> 07:31.243
Ugh! Zap!
Wha?

07:31.276 --> 07:33.378
[ Whoosh ]

07:33.411 --> 07:35.347
Well, that was terrifying.

07:37.983 --> 07:41.219
I've tried everything I can
think of to make Simon remember.

07:41.253 --> 07:43.288
Is there something I'm missing?

07:43.321 --> 07:45.157
What am I doing wrong?

07:45.190 --> 07:48.627
Maybe you're going after someone
who doesn't exist anymore.

07:48.661 --> 07:50.162
Why not take him as he is?

07:50.195 --> 07:53.732
After all, you've been through
a lot of changes yourself.

07:53.766 --> 07:55.901
You're making a lot of sense,
Tiny Manticore.

07:55.934 --> 07:59.972
We're like two shadows,
two ghosts caught in limbo.

08:00.005 --> 08:02.741
It sounds depressing
when you say it that way.

08:02.775 --> 08:04.509
Think of a different way
to say it.

08:04.542 --> 08:07.813
[ Crying softly ]

08:07.846 --> 08:09.014
[ Sighs heavily ]

08:09.047 --> 08:10.182
Wenk.

08:10.215 --> 08:11.984
Oh, uh, just stretching.

08:12.017 --> 08:13.318
Wenk?

08:13.351 --> 08:15.654
The date?
Uh, yeah, it went great.

08:15.688 --> 08:17.455
I don't know about
a second date, though.

08:17.489 --> 08:19.024
I don't wanna be that guy

08:19.057 --> 08:21.026
who just hangs out with
his girlfriend all the time

08:21.059 --> 08:23.295
and doesn't see his friends.

08:23.328 --> 08:25.363
Man, I wanna be that guy
so bad.

08:25.397 --> 08:26.765
[ Whoosh ]

08:26.799 --> 08:30.168
Hey, I was just talking about
you to my penguin.

08:30.202 --> 08:31.670
Have you met Gunter?

08:31.704 --> 08:34.139
Yes. I kidnapped him
that one time.

08:34.172 --> 08:36.508
Look, Simon --
I mean, Ice King.

08:36.541 --> 08:39.544
Yeah, who's this Simon guy
you keep yakking about?

08:39.577 --> 08:41.313
Should I be jealous?

08:41.346 --> 08:44.016
He's somebody I knew
a long time ago.

08:44.049 --> 08:46.384
Hey, you still into
bird watching?

08:46.418 --> 08:48.220
Watch this.

08:48.253 --> 08:49.487
[ Electricity crackles ]
Mmm...zow!

08:49.521 --> 08:51.489
[ Birds chirping ]
[ Laughs ] Amazing!

08:51.523 --> 08:55.360
[ Laughs ]
Such beautiful birds!

08:55.393 --> 08:57.395
They're all for you, Ice King.

08:57.429 --> 08:59.732
Woof. What a bust.

08:59.765 --> 09:02.500
These are
some low-grade fairies.

09:02.534 --> 09:05.237
My magic battery is
going to su--

09:05.270 --> 09:07.639
Who's this dancing with
the I.K.?

09:07.672 --> 09:09.074
[ Electricity crackles ]

09:09.107 --> 09:11.376
Bird friend! [ Laughs ]

09:11.409 --> 09:13.846
How delightful.

09:13.879 --> 09:16.081
[ Laughing ]

09:16.114 --> 09:17.582
Ha! [ Sighs ]

09:17.615 --> 09:20.318
Huh? Where did
the weird lady go?

09:20.352 --> 09:22.921
Uh...well,
when you weren't looking,

09:22.955 --> 09:25.023
her -- her mom showed up
and told her that

09:25.057 --> 09:27.492
her old boyfriend wanted to be
with her again,

09:27.525 --> 09:29.728
and they ran off together.
The end.

09:29.762 --> 09:31.163
Her mom?

09:31.196 --> 09:34.332
Well, I gotta go.

09:34.366 --> 09:36.534
I almost forgot!

09:36.568 --> 09:39.037
Surprise!

09:41.539 --> 09:44.777
[ Crying, chewing ]

09:44.810 --> 09:47.780
[ Groans ]

09:47.813 --> 09:49.581
I wonder if my roomie
has any more

09:49.614 --> 09:51.416
of these soothing doughnuts.

09:51.449 --> 09:53.786
Only one way to find out!

09:53.819 --> 09:56.755
♪♪

09:56.789 --> 10:01.927
Patience:
Elemental, elemental.

10:01.960 --> 10:04.797
Stand, do not sit.

10:04.830 --> 10:06.131
Cool.

10:06.164 --> 10:09.534
Elemental, Elemental.

10:09.567 --> 10:11.970
Can not quit.

10:12.004 --> 10:14.306
Weird Lady!

10:14.339 --> 10:15.974
Blast him!

10:16.008 --> 10:17.976
[ Humming ]

10:18.010 --> 10:19.277
Eee.

10:19.311 --> 10:20.813
[ Zaps ]

10:20.846 --> 10:22.747
Then everything went nuts.

10:22.781 --> 10:25.884
There was all this light
and noise.

10:25.918 --> 10:29.621
I grabbed as many penguins
as I could -- one.

10:29.654 --> 10:31.323
But now that you're here,

10:31.356 --> 10:33.491
we can go back
and save Weird Lady.

10:33.525 --> 10:35.727
Sounds like we got
our first lead.

10:35.760 --> 10:39.965
All we needed was...
a little patience.

10:42.534 --> 10:46.438
♪ Come along with me

10:46.471 --> 10:50.843
♪ And the butterflies and bees

10:53.678 --> 10:55.981
This party is so crazy!
